:'''Pythias:''' Phainon, you once said you wanted to leave Aedes Elysiae and explore the wider world. How's that going?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Everything's ready now.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504112103-->
::'''Pythias:''' Good to hear. Life here is quiet, but out there... you'll need to stay sharp.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} There are still a few things I haven't figured out...
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504112105-->
::'''Pythias:''' Hehe, ever since childhood, you've always had a careful mind &mdash; always planing ahead.
::'''Pythias:''' But it's okay. Even if you decide to stay, I'll still support you. There's value in adventure, yes &mdash; but living a quiet, steady life is also a choice worth making.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504112107-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504112107-->
:'''Pythias:''' Just don't pressure yourself. Whatever you choose, as long as it's what your heart tells you... that's enough.
:'''Pythias:''' As for the info of the Grove you asked me to look into, I've managed to dig up a few leads.
:'''Pythias:''' Though I've never been there myself, they say the sages of its various schools are all brilliant minds &mdash; learned, skilled, and deeply respected. Studying under one of them would surely take you far.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} In that case... I've gotta see this myself.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Just wait till I come back a master!
:<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504112112-->
:'''Pythias:''' Hehe, that's the spirit. But... I've also heard the Grove of Epiphany places great value on open debate and independent thinking. The academic scene is extremely free &mdash; so much so that bizarre and radical theories pop up all the time.
:'''Pythias:''' If you really plan to go, you'll need to keep your eyes sharp. Learn what you can, but don't lose your way.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'll keep that in mind.
:<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504112115-->
:'''Pythias:''' Well, I've rambled enough &mdash; you must've had your fill. Off with you now.
